<TITLE> Education policy draft goes to PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 2 (bdnews24.com)Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid submitted the draft national education policy to the prime minister on Monday, with an expected recommendation to extend primary education to eight years. After his meeting with prime minister Sheikh Hasina, Nahid told reporters the draft had been formulated in line with recommendations from the national education policy formulation committee, headed by national professor Kabir Chowdhury. On Sep 2, the committee submitted policy paper to the education ministry, with separate provisions for primary, secondary and higher education as well as technical and madrasa education. Nahid said the education policy would be finalised this year and implemented from the coming year. Details of the newly drafted policy will be posted on the education ministry's website till Sep 30, said Nahid. bd
